{
  "stem": "14060.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "These are the people who are not idiots, who are clever, educated, intelligent people, knowingly over the periods of time after the war-- let it be what was before the war-- still had the audacity to make such a statement.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And that is, I think, what people in future generations should remember.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Now coming back to the period of relative tranquility in the '30s, I remember that the first serious anti-Jewish legislations were brought in 1935, '36 period under the prime ministership of a man called Gombos.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And that was a time when they seriously started to restrict educationwise, businesswise, connectionwise the people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "You know, it was basically the Nuremberg laws, which in somewhat may be different format were instituted in Hungary, Hungary being at all times an ally of Germany, of course.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I remember in later years, in '37, '38 and so on, that they-- people overnight used a certain chemical on shop-- Jewish shop windows.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't have a shop, so it didn't affect us personally.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they put on Jew in Hungarian, zsido, and they put on it a writing-- it wasn't graffiti.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a chemical which went into the glass and you could not remove it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Say, don't buy, this is a Jewish shop, that sort of things, more or less, which I think you may have seen in a different form, which the Nazis did in Berlin and other German cities.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the intimidation slowly but surely progressed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was really the attitude of the Jews, I presume, that this is another passing period and times will become better.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Do you remember what you felt at that time or--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would say to you this, that the-- one was basically mentally educated to accept it, because we did not have pogroms.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
